<section id="accordions">
    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <details open>
        <summary><strong>Why 'parot'?</strong></summary>
        <p>
            We loved where Twitter was going. But feel it is moving in the wrong direction.
        </p>
    </details>
    <details open>
        <summary><strong>Real time conversation are hard to keep up with.</strong></summary>
        <p>
            Users can focus on the conversations they engage with through context filters, hiding all non-active conversations while engaged, but allowing users to switch in and out of their contexts quickly and easily.
        </p>
    </details>
    <details open>
        <summary><strong>Is there only a single feed?</strong></summary>
        <p>
            We break 'feeds' into channels. Users can browse the global channel, or create a new channel to organise or filter the content they want to see.
        </p>
    </details>
    <details open>
        <summary><strong>Why Parot over Threads/BlueSky?</strong></summary>
        <p>
            Our objective is to build a new communication tool that is different to what we have today. These apps are nice, but very similar to Twitter.
        </p>
    </details>
</section>